%% TrustyAI Service Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.2+
    participant TAS as TAS Controller
    participant LMES as LMES Controller
    participant GORCH as GORCH Controller
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP TLS
    participant TASvc as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant EvalPod as Evaluation Pod<br/>+ Driver Sidecar
    participant Orch as Orchestrator<br/>8032/TCP HTTPS
    participant InfSvc as KServe InferenceService
    participant DB as Database<br/>JDBC TLS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: Create TrustyAIService CR<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>TAS: Watch event
    TAS->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment + kube-rbac-proxy<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    TAS->>K8sAPI: Create Service, Route, PVC<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    TAS->>InfSvc: Patch with MM_PAYLOAD_PROCESSORS<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1a: TrustyAI API Access
    User->>Route: POST /api/...<br/>HTTPS TLS (reencrypt)
    Route->>RBAC: Forward<br/>TLS (service-serving cert)
    RBAC->>RBAC: SubjectAccessReview check
    RBAC->>TASvc: Proxy request<br/>HTTP (localhost)
    TASvc->>DB: Store/retrieve data<br/>JDBC TLS (optional)
    TASvc-->>RBAC: Response
    RBAC-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: JSON Response

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: LMEvalJob Execution
    User->>K8sAPI: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>LMES: Watch event
    LMES->>K8sAPI: Create evaluation Pod + driver sidecar<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    EvalPod->>InfSvc: Evaluate model<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    EvalPod->>S3: Load offline data<br/>HTTPS AWS IAM
    EvalPod->>K8sAPI: Update status (via driver)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    LMES->>K8sAPI: Update LMEvalJob status<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Guardrails Orchestration
    User->>K8sAPI: Create GuardrailsOrchestrator CR<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>GORCH: Watch event
    GORCH->>K8sAPI: Discover InferenceServices<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    GORCH->>K8sAPI: Create multi-container Deployment<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    User->>Route: POST /api/...<br/>HTTPS TLS (reencrypt)
    Route->>RBAC: Forward (8432/TCP)<br/>TLS
    RBAC->>Orch: Proxy request<br/>HTTPS 8032/TCP
    Orch->>InfSvc: Generator request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (configurable)
    Orch->>InfSvc: Detector request(s)<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (configurable)
    InfSvc-->>Orch: Detection results
    Orch-->>RBAC: Orchestrated response
    RBAC-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: JSON Response
